Drive-thru Meet the Teacher! üöòü•∞üêæ

We cannot wait to meet you!!! We will be 6 feet away but want a chance to meet your sweet faces outside, from your car, 6 feet away, before we protect each other and use masks during school. Please pull through the regular drop off line and circle back down FM 1242 and around the football field as teachers will be lined up along the gravel road holding signs to greet you!

Elementary students may drop off supplies with administration at their table. 6-12 please bring your supplies the first day.

Parents, expect a video early next week that will explain dropoff and pickup procedures and a few other things you will want to know!

Please share this so all our friends get the word!

post_text: All athletes that have a physical on file will not need a new physical for this school year, per new UIL guidance. To check on whether a physical is on file, please contact Coach Morgan for boys or Coach Snow for girls. This year student-athletes will need Concussion Acknowledgement Form, Sudden Cardiac Awareness Form, Steroid Agreement Form, and Acknowledgement of Rules Form that are in the office or can be found on https://www.uiltexas.org/athletics/forms . These must be turned in before the start of sports practices.

post_text:
Registration packets for returning students are available in the front office on Tuesday and Thursdays from 9-3. We are hoping to get a jump start on the registration process with the unusual circumstances around the coming school year. Please feel free to stop by! The front door may be locked but we will be here. Please knock and we will be with you. If you cannot make it during these hours, please contact us at the school and we can make other arrangements.

New students for the 2020-2021 school year, who live in the district, can also stop by for a packet. First time enrollment (PreK and Kindergarten usually) student packets are also available. However, these students will need more information to build their permanent file! Transfer applications are also available.

If you have any questions, please feel free to contact us at the school!

Bynum ISD would like to welcome our new athletic director and head football coach, Casey Morgan, to the district. Coach Morgan has spent the last few years as assistant coach at Blum and prior to that was an assistant coach at Gordon. We are excited to have Coach Morgan become part of the Bulldog family and are looking forward to a great year!

The UIL will be allowing Summer Strength and Condition workouts to begin June 8. As soon as we have summer workout times and schedules available we will share them.

Before Spring Break, 4th grade science was doing an experiment to see how dirty pieces of bread would get based on how clean or dirty their hands were. The amazing Mrs. Sumpter wanted to share the results with her students and our followers.

Especially now, this is such a good reminder of just how dirty our hands can get, and how even using just hand sanitizer can make a difference! Do your part and practice healthy, safe habits!

We are beginning to see an increased number of students that have tested positive for the flu along with students with flu symptoms. Please do not send your children to school if they are sick and do not send them back to school until they are fever free for 24 hours. If you give your children Ibuprofen, Tylenol, Motrin, etc. to reduce the fever and send them to school they are still contagious. Thank you for being considerate of the other students in our school.

Thank you.

Hill County Fair
January 11 at 1:36 PM ¬∑

Creative Arts registration ends tonight!
Monday, January 27th will be check-in for your items. Doors open at 7:30 and run until 6 pm. We ask schools to please have their items there by 5 pm. The Creative Arts Division opens to the public at 1 pm on Wednesday, January 29th. Youth auction sign up is Wednesday, January 29th from 1 pm to 7 pm and Thursday, January 30th from 9 am to 2 pm. It is the responsibility of the exhibitor to see his/her name gets on the auction list. All Grand Champion, Reserve Champion and First Place items are eligible for auction. Participants may sell only one item. All items not in the auction must be picked up Thursday, January 30th from 4 pm to 7 pm or Friday, January 31st from 10 am to 4 pm. Please remember all no -auction items must be picked up by 4 pm on Friday, January 31st! Unfortunately we can not save items!
We look forward to seeing you at the Hill County Fair!

The JH Football game tonight in Lometa has been canceled. Lometa ISD has been on a soft lockdown since around 11:15 due to a high speed chase that ended with the suspect fleeing on foot. We will see you tomorrow at our pink out pep rally followed by the HS Football game at 7:30.

Due to a shortage of officials, we are needing to change our football schedule. We will now host JH football here vs. Cranfills Gap at 5:30 on Thursday, immediately following we will have the HS football game also vs. Cranfills Gap. We apologize for any inconvenience this may cause, but we are hoping to give our student-athletes an opportunity to play.

This change in schedule has created a desperate need for concession volunteers on Thursday night. If you are able to help, please respond to this post, call the school, or contact Chrisi Cordell. ANY help is greatly appreciated.

Thank you!

shared_text:
Bynum ISD
July 16, 2019 at 8:23 PM ¬∑

Reminder: Physicals for High School athletes will need to be completed prior to participation in two-a-days.(August 1st - Girls; August 5th - Boys) Junior High physicals
will need to be completed by the first day of school.

Physicals can be scheduled at the Clinic or with your family Physician. Physicals are required for incoming 7th, 9th and 11th graders. **Any athlete who had an injury requiring a doctor's release (last school year) must also
have a physical.

Packets can be picked up in the front office for JH and HS athletes with paperwork that will need to be returned on the first day back.

Enjoy the rest of your summer. We look forward to a successful year!

post_text: Hi my name is Jana Geesaman and I will be teaching HS Math. I am a true Oregonian moving to Texas with my husband. We both enjoy traveling the U.S. on our motorcycles, working outside, and gaming. I started teaching in East LA but spent the bulk of my teaching at a rural school in Sandy, OR; the gateway to Mt. Hood. I am excited to take on this new adventure of ours in Texas and become a Bulldog!

post_text: Is this your dog? He has been hanging out at the school but really needs to go home. There is a good chance that he does not even have a home. We've checked the local shelters and they are full. If anyone is interested in taking him please call the school. We have put him in a kennel for now to keep him off of the highway but that is only a short term solution.

post_text:
This week is our last wave of STAAR testing! We cannot wait to see our kids SHINE!

Monday- Math STAAR Grades 3, 4, 6, 7 and 5&8 Retake
Tuesday- Reading STAAR Grades 3, 4, 6, 7 and 5&8 Retake
Wednesday- Science STAAR Grades 5&8
Thursday- Social Studies STAAR Grade8

Please help your child do their best by encouraging them at home with positivity, making sure they get a good night's sleep, and feeding them a healthy breakfast. We appreciate ALL of the parental support we have received this year!

post_text: Freshmen are working on Enlightenment thinkers in World History. The class was split into 7 groups, and each group got an Enlightenment thinker to read over. Then, they had to design their posters. We will have a ‚ÄúGallery Walk‚Äù to gather notes on the other philosophers. We are super proud of the work and focus this group has put in this week!
